Articles.Content: Very thanks

Very thanks

So chutes. Much drag. Wow.

I just started using the .90 realchutes, and in my mission I found that Jeb, a pilot, was able to repack the MK16 parachute, despite not being an engineer? Will this be fixed in an upcoming update?

Edit: I see from an earlier post this is already being looked into. Have an excellent cruise!

Edited December 27, 2014 by TThor

Since updating from 1.2.6.1 to 1.2.6.2 I am getting a bug when using the mk16 parachute. Once the rocket passes 6000m the center of mass suddenly shifts way below where the craft is. this makes the camera focus on a point below the rocket and makes the physics go a little crazy. I'm using a few other mods so it may be a compatibility issue. Is anyone else having this?

I'm seeing that too with multiple different parachutes

also I'm seeing parachutes burst into flame a couple of minutes into a launch (tantares TST decopler chutes)

Since updating from 1.2.6.1 to 1.2.6.2 I am getting a bug when using the mk16 parachute. Once the rocket passes 6000m the center of mass suddenly shifts way below where the craft is. this makes the camera focus on a point below the rocket and makes the physics go a little crazy. I'm using a few other mods so it may be a compatibility issue. Is anyone else having this?

I'm having the same issue. The chute doesn't show up in my staging menu and gives me a "cannot deploy" error when I initiate blastoff. Above a certain height (not sure exactly what it is) I get a red message saying unsafe to deploy chute and shortly thereafter the camera just stops and the rocket keeps going.

I've found that if I go to the action group menu and select single chute model from the menu it works correctly. Unfortunately just starting a career the action menu is not available and with that being the only chute, it completely breaks the game.

It seems at least some of the problem is there's an issue with it not selecting a chute model for the stock chutes. I couldn't find the settings for this in the files though so I wasn't able to try a fix.

Since updating from 1.2.6.1 to 1.2.6.2 I am getting a bug when using the mk16 parachute. Once the rocket passes 6000m the center of mass suddenly shifts way below where the craft is. this makes the camera focus on a point below the rocket and makes the physics go a little crazy. I'm using a few other mods so it may be a compatibility issue. Is anyone else having this?

I had that same bug with a previous version of Realchutes, where the stock parachutess had this problem. The only fix I had was not using stock chutes
I can confirm that even with no other mods installed this still occurs. is there somewhere that I can get the old version of real chutes?

I can confirm that even with no other mods installed this still occurs. is there somewhere that I can get the old version of real chutes?

If you go to the kerbalstuff link at the start of this thread and click on versions, you should be able to download previous versions.

I just restarted with the previous version and found I had to rebuild the rocket I was using from scratch but it worked fine after that.

I'm also having this error. Console log doesn't show anything useful either.

After this all hell breaks loose and KCT, Kerbal Engineer Redux and Enhanced Navball throw nullrefs endlessly. I haven't even bothered trying with no other mods due to that not helping according to others above.

Mod Author is on vacation and won't be back until Jan.

In the meantime, from experience, he'd prefer FULL output_log.txt for diagnosing errors.

In the past, the phantom CoM and flight go nuts could be attributed to use of previously created craft with RC part(s) on it. I had this happen to me many times. I had to pull in those craft, remove the RC part and then pull new part and put back. That cured problem for me, but who knows'

Good luck...

Cheers.

Have the same issue with camera center shift at 6000m. The craft flies up and the camera lags behind. Also chutes are not being staged, they are shown in stages in VAB but when I go to the launchpad, they are not there, although I can still activate them pressing space... weird huh?

So here is output log: https://www.dropbox.com/s/0srunicb4yp4ec3/output_log.txt?dl=0 , I started the game, launched simple ship, experienced a bug, crashed, reverted, exited the game.

Hope this helps, cheers.

Since updating from 1.2.6.1 to 1.2.6.2 I am getting a bug when using the mk16 parachute. Once the rocket passes 6000m the center of mass suddenly shifts way below where the craft is. this makes the camera focus on a point below the rocket and makes the physics go a little crazy. I'm using a few other mods so it may be a compatibility issue. Is anyone else having this?

Same error. Rolled back for now. Thanks for the effort anyway Chris. Enjoy your vacation.
Think I know the issue, thatll teach me to do last minute untested changes. Gonna try a quick fix, hold on to your pants folks.

In the past, the phantom CoM and flight go nuts could be attributed to use of previously created craft with RC part(s) on it. I had this happen to me many times. I had to pull in those craft, remove the RC part and then pull new part and put back. That cured problem for me, but who knows'

Good luck...

Cheers.

It still does it even with a new craft unfortunately.

I was driving myself nuts trying to figure out the problem because I remember it happened before with a previous version as well.

Thanks for getting on this stupid_chris!

In the forum thread for this mod created by, jfjohnny5

[0.90] K2 Command Pod: Two Kerbal stock-alike pod

http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/104925-0-90-K2-Command-Pod-Two-Kerbal-stock-alike-pod?p=1631957&viewfull=1#post1631957

KSP member, visivante

Posted has posted this:

"I can't figure out why, whenever I use this pod the camera lowers its focus away from the craft after every 6000m. The camera slowly starts to lag behind the craft until a minute or so later the craft is 1km above where the camera is focused. It looks exactly like this.

I don't have any camera mods installed. And it's a very sudden and very consistent effect at that altitude when only using this pod. Any guesses? I'd love to be able to use this!"

You may want to let jfjohnny5 know in case the root cause is similar.

Alright guys, from what it seems, it only affects stock chutes. I'd reccoment only using RealChute parts until I fixed, I found what's causing the problem and I'll use the one hour bus ride to the boat to try to fix it, can't guarantee anything.

If someone can post a complete output_log.txt without only RealChute as a mod, that would greatly help.
OMG, I wondered which MOD was causing the camera to shift away from the vessel! Was going nuts - Just by coincidence I read these posts.
